<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-02-1306 </DOCNO><TEXT>Criticism is made of the authors of ICRP Publication 51 for includingambient, directional and individual dose equivalents in the categoryof dosimetric quantities. Criticism is also made of the 'rigging' ofinstruments to try to fit the conversion curve between the physical dosimetricquantities and dose equivalents. Replies to these criticisms are givenby the Editor-in-Chief of the Radiation Protection Dosimetry Journal.(U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>